[src:trpc-typesafe/global-objects-promise] Upon provision of an initial promise, a chain of promises can follow.
[src:trpc-typesafe/global-objects-promise] The chain is composed of `.then()` calls, and typically (but not necessarily) has a single `.catch()` at the end, optionally followed by `.finally()`.
[src:trpc-typesafe/global-objects-promise] In this example, the promise chain is initiated by a custom-written `new Promise()` construct; but in actual practice, promise chains more typically start with an API function (written by someone else) that returns a promise.
